root_cause: Agent sandbox blocks deepchem/pickle imports during development, causing pipreqs to not detect these packages, which means DGL is not installed in evaluation container
fix_description: instruction_override tells agent to include proper import statements for ScScoreModel and CircularFingerprint; this triggers pipreqs detection and DGL post-install hook
notes: Docker base image has Python 3.10, TensorFlow 2.17 pre-installed. The issue was pipreqs detection, not TensorFlow availability.
